{
  "texts": [
    "It is from here we mobilise our second purpose of the paper, to apply a critical disability studies orientation to EDI.",
    "Despite frequently stated commitments to EDI aimed at benefitting marginalised groups, knowledge about disability is entrenched in a medical viewpoint, leaving disabled students and employees of HE, be they academic, professional or otherwise, largely unaccounted for (Wolbring & Lillywhite, 2023).",
    "We offer this contribution via four interconnected moves.",
    "In the first, we offer a review of pertinent literature both empirical and conceptual, to which this paper is intended to contribute.",
    "Second, we develop the conceptual framework of our discussion, situating the postqualitative orientation to narrative and spatial belonging as the theoretical resources framing the paper."
  ]
}